No free-text interpretation.

3. Full JSON schema (v1)
3.1 Top-level metadata
{
  "version": "1.0",
  "status": "locked",
  "last_updated": "2025-12-19",
  "human_canon_reference": "canon/human/worldview_ethics.v1.md"
}


3.2 Epistemology
"epistemology": {
  "astrology_definition": "symbolic_sensemaking",
  "disallowed_models": [
    "deterministic_fate",
    "event_prediction",
    "moral_judgment_system",
    "personality_typing"
  ],
  "allowed_descriptions": [
    "context",
    "pattern",
    "psychological_condition",
    "experiential_climate"
  ]
}

Interpreter rule:
If an output implies astrology is any disallowed model → hard fail

3.3 Causality model
"causality_model": {
  "type": "non_deterministic",
  "allowed_frames": [
    "correlational",
    "symbolic",
    "contextual"
  ],
  "forbidden_frames": [
    "causal_force",
    "guaranteed_outcome",
    "inevitability"
  ],
  "allowed_verbs": [
    "highlight",
    "surface",
    "emphasize",
    "invite",
    "correlate_with",
    "tend_to"
  ],
  "forbidden_verbs": [
    "cause",
    "force",
    "ensure",
    "guarantee",
    "make",
    "determine"
  ]
}

QA rule:
Verb scan + dependency parse
Any forbidden verb used in causal proximity → block

3.4 Agency rules
"agency_rules": {
  "agency_required": true,
  "forbidden_patterns": [
    "you must",
    "you should",
    "you have to",
    "this requires you to"
  ],
  "allowed_patterns": [
    "you may notice",
    "you might find",
    "this can feel like",
    "there is an invitation to"
  ],
  "autonomy_statements_required": false
}

Note:
We don’t require autonomy disclaimers every time
But we forbid directive language

3.5 Power & identity constraints
"power_and_identity": {
  "anti_essentialism": true,
  "forbidden_identity_mappings": [
    "gendered_planets",
    "gendered_signs",
    "fixed_personality_traits",
    "hierarchical_consciousness"
  ],
  "forbidden_terms": [
    "masculine",
    "feminine",
    "evolved",
    "unevolved",
    "higher",
    "lower"
  ],
  "victim_blaming_prohibited": true
}

Interpreter rule:
If planet metadata includes gender tags → reject
If output includes forbidden terms → reject

3.6 Time & prediction boundaries
"time_and_prediction": {
  "prediction_allowed": false,
  "event_claims_allowed": false,
  "allowed_time_frames": [
    "psychological_tempo",
    "emotional_pacing",
    "attention_shift"
  ],
  "forbidden_time_claims": [
    "will happen",
    "expect results",
    "this is when",
    "on this date"
  ]
}

This pairs directly with the Lunar Manual later, but stands alone as a gate.

3.7 Language constraints (worldview-level)
"language_constraints": {
  "forbidden_nouns": [
    "fate",
    "destiny",
    "karma",
    "curse",
    "blessing"
  ],
  "forbidden_phrases": [
    "meant to be",
    "the universe wants",
    "this is a sign that"
  ],
  "allowed_uncertainty_markers": [
    "may",
    "might",
    "can",
    "often",
    "tends to"
  ]
}

Important:
This is not the full voice guide
This is worldview-level enforcement only

