Metrics

4. How this is used in code (conceptual)
Interpreter side:
validateWorldview(outputText, worldviewRules);

QA side:
const violations = detectWorldviewViolations(
  outputText,
  worldviewRules
);

if (violations.some(v => v.severity === "blocking")) {
  throw new WorldviewViolationError(violations);
}

No heuristics.
Just rule evaluation.

5. What not to do
Do not:
Encode long prose explanations here
Add “temporary exceptions”
Let prompts override this
Soft-fail violations
This file is constitutional law, not guidance.
